1
00:00:06,100 --> 00:00:09,100
=Episode 4 (Part 2)=
=Dangerous Variables=

2
00:00:09,110 --> 00:00:10,720
Gentlemen,

3
00:00:10,720 --> 00:00:12,190
what's going through your minds?

4
00:00:19,680 --> 00:00:21,470
I want a date.

5
00:00:21,470 --> 00:00:23,360
I want a date too.

6
00:00:24,150 --> 00:00:24,360
Wait.

7
00:00:24,360 --> 00:00:25,600
I'm heading off the island too.

8
00:00:27,870 --> 00:00:30,440
Friends, give me this one chance.

9
00:00:31,870 --> 00:00:32,560
Hello.

10
00:00:32,560 --> 00:00:33,560
You're pretty quick.

11
00:00:33,560 --> 00:00:34,840
Of course.

12
00:00:34,840 --> 00:00:36,040
She's always quick.

13
00:00:36,240 --> 00:00:37,590
Is that so?

14
00:00:38,080 --> 00:00:40,080
Attention, islanders.

15
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:42,840
Date arrangements have been made
by women.

16
00:00:43,470 --> 00:00:44,000
Let's go.

17
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:44,880
I think

18
00:00:45,520 --> 00:00:46,430
we need to have a chat.

19
00:00:51,840 --> 00:00:52,560
I'm leaving.

20
00:00:52,560 --> 00:00:53,150
Goodbye.

21
00:00:53,150 --> 00:00:54,150
You're not leaving.

22
00:00:54,630 --> 00:00:55,840
What's going on?

23
00:00:56,110 --> 00:00:56,840
I think…

24
00:00:56,840 --> 00:00:58,310
I think you should hear me out.

25
00:00:58,310 --> 00:00:58,620
Go on.

26
00:00:58,620 --> 00:01:00,520
Since you just arrived,
take some time to settle in.

27
00:01:00,520 --> 00:01:00,790
Right.

28
00:01:00,790 --> 00:01:02,950
You've got to
experience the Balance Island.

29
00:01:02,950 --> 00:01:03,430
Exactly.

30
00:01:03,430 --> 00:01:05,230
Don't be like Jie,

31
00:01:05,230 --> 00:01:06,310
in and out three times.

32
00:01:06,310 --> 00:01:07,950
We still need to win this game.

33
00:01:08,550 --> 00:01:10,360
So, what are we doing later?

34
00:01:10,720 --> 00:01:12,720
After the game,
we can head out for some fun.

35
00:01:13,680 --> 00:01:15,120
So you think you can head out?

36
00:01:15,910 --> 00:01:16,760
With who exactly?

37
00:01:17,230 --> 00:01:18,310
Can I go out by myself?

38
00:01:20,230 --> 00:01:20,950
Let's head back.

39
00:01:21,270 --> 00:01:22,590
Go back and get some real rest.

40
00:01:22,590 --> 00:01:23,110
Take a break.

41
00:01:23,110 --> 00:01:25,270
We'll leave the island this afternoon.

42
00:01:25,440 --> 00:01:25,870
Let's go.

43
00:01:26,120 --> 00:01:27,590
I'm leaving the island, while you…

44
00:01:27,590 --> 00:01:29,000
Take a proper break here.

45
00:01:36,360 --> 00:01:37,270
We…

46
00:01:37,270 --> 00:01:38,630
We're leaving.

47
00:01:39,910 --> 00:01:41,190
Get some extra rest.

48
00:01:47,490 --> 00:01:48,690
What were you struggling with?

49
00:01:49,550 --> 00:01:50,440
It's really tough.

50
00:01:50,440 --> 00:01:52,590
Because we can't set up two dates
for one person.

51
00:01:53,190 --> 00:01:55,910
You mean it can't be one versus many?

52
00:01:55,910 --> 00:01:56,270
Exactly.

53
00:01:56,270 --> 00:01:59,230
It can only be one-on-one,
or another pair.

54
00:02:01,230 --> 00:02:02,590
Then it shouldn't be that hard.

55
00:02:02,590 --> 00:02:03,100
The one left…

56
00:02:03,100 --> 00:02:03,630
Still tricky.

57
00:02:03,630 --> 00:02:04,040
There's...

58
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:04,760
One person left.

59
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:05,480
No.

60
00:02:05,480 --> 00:02:07,590
Maybe someone wants to know new people.

61
00:02:15,630 --> 00:02:19,320
See you.

62
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:26,750
I kind of had a feeling.

63
00:02:26,750 --> 00:02:27,720
(Zizheng's room)
Today,

64
00:02:27,720 --> 00:02:28,390
I can't get out.

65
00:02:28,630 --> 00:02:30,030
I just wanted to go on one date.

66
00:02:30,030 --> 00:02:30,960
You'll get your chance.

67
00:02:30,960 --> 00:02:31,850
I want to go out too.

68
00:02:31,910 --> 00:02:33,030
Honestly,

69
00:02:33,240 --> 00:02:34,600
Yijia probably won't pick me.

70
00:02:34,750 --> 00:02:35,630
It'll be you.

71
00:02:35,630 --> 00:02:35,910
No way.

72
00:02:35,910 --> 00:02:36,360
It's you.

73
00:02:36,470 --> 00:02:37,240
No.

74
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:37,830
Impossible.

75
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:40,520
Yijia just said something to me

76
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:42,110
and half of me just froze inside.

77
00:02:42,110 --> 00:02:42,960
What did she say?

78
00:02:42,960 --> 00:02:43,670
She said,

79
00:02:43,670 --> 00:02:47,030
"Maybe someone wants to know new people."

80
00:02:47,240 --> 00:02:48,270
That sounds like...

81
00:02:48,750 --> 00:02:49,440
A hint.

82
00:02:49,440 --> 00:02:51,630
In Shanghai dialect,
we call it "give you a nudge".

83
00:02:52,110 --> 00:02:52,880
Do you

84
00:02:52,880 --> 00:02:54,160
regret the choice you made?

85
00:02:58,440 --> 00:02:59,650
I'm not really torn about it,

86
00:02:59,650 --> 00:03:00,720
but I do think it's tough.

87
00:03:03,240 --> 00:03:05,030
My priority is definitely Zhang.

88
00:03:06,220 --> 00:03:09,020
(Chen Yijia is choosing
her date partner.)

89
00:03:09,030 --> 00:03:11,030
But I keep feeling like,

90
00:03:11,030 --> 00:03:12,430
(Date Arrangement Card. Chen Yijia)
we can

91
00:03:12,430 --> 00:03:14,550
(Ding Wanning & Zhao Enda)
meet anytime on the island.

92
00:03:14,550 --> 00:03:16,440
We have plenty of chances to hang out.

93
00:03:18,980 --> 00:03:24,900
(Date Arrangement Card:
Chen Yijia & Yang Tianyu)

94
00:03:24,910 --> 00:03:25,830
Since Zhan left,

95
00:03:25,830 --> 00:03:28,440
I've started seeing this place
like an arena.

96
00:03:28,440 --> 00:03:29,600
What I'm thinking is,

97
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:31,110
one more vote

98
00:03:31,110 --> 00:03:32,110
wouldn't hurt, right?

99
00:03:32,670 --> 00:03:35,440
So when Tianyu showed me

100
00:03:35,440 --> 00:03:38,110
just a bit of interest in me...

101
00:03:38,320 --> 00:03:41,080
Then if you win, who would you choose?

102
00:03:41,440 --> 00:03:42,630
You want me to ask you out?

103
00:03:42,630 --> 00:03:43,440
Sure.

104
00:03:44,160 --> 00:03:45,440
Alright.

105
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:46,830
I think this is actually

106
00:03:46,830 --> 00:03:48,470
a smarter way to get votes.

107
00:03:48,910 --> 00:03:50,160
So I filled in Tianyu's name.

108
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,470
I think she's kinda into...

109
00:03:55,470 --> 00:03:57,220
(She really likes Tianyu)
Tianyu.

110
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:59,190
Honestly, newcomers have an advantage.

111
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:00,220
Yeah.

112
00:04:00,220 --> 00:04:02,060
Everyone wants to know more about him.

113
00:04:02,060 --> 00:04:03,240
Especially someone like Angus.

114
00:04:03,240 --> 00:04:04,800
(Yang Tianyu)
Who wouldn't be curious?

115
00:04:06,110 --> 00:04:06,720
He showed up

116
00:04:06,720 --> 00:04:07,930
and every other guy's chances

117
00:04:07,930 --> 00:04:09,030
just dropped by half.

118
00:04:10,030 --> 00:04:10,720
Yeah.

119
00:04:10,720 --> 00:04:11,800
But honestly,

120
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:13,190
if it's about competitions,

121
00:04:13,190 --> 00:04:15,520
I can't really beat Angus and Guan.

122
00:04:15,520 --> 00:04:17,200
Have you seen the huge muscles on them?

123
00:04:18,550 --> 00:04:20,950
Didn't expect dark horses to show up halfway.

124
00:04:24,640 --> 00:04:25,440
I told you already,

125
00:04:25,440 --> 00:04:26,510
what I want is...

126
00:04:26,510 --> 00:04:28,440
to get to know the new male guest.

127
00:04:28,440 --> 00:04:29,670
But if I really chose Guan,

128
00:04:29,670 --> 00:04:30,600
you'd be upset, right?

129
00:04:30,760 --> 00:04:31,930
Did you actually choose him?

130
00:04:32,230 --> 00:04:33,760
I feel like maybe you did.

131
00:04:36,350 --> 00:04:37,590
You're not saying anything.

132
00:04:37,590 --> 00:04:38,350
Password accepted.

133
00:04:43,950 --> 00:04:45,640
You didn't really pick Guan, right?

134
00:04:47,550 --> 00:04:47,820
I mean

135
00:04:47,820 --> 00:04:48,890
you didn't pick him, right?

136
00:04:48,890 --> 00:04:50,390
Did you choose him in the first group?

137
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:51,790
You mean my dating partner?

138
00:04:51,790 --> 00:04:52,200
Yes.

139
00:04:52,200 --> 00:04:53,230
Did you actually pick him?

140
00:04:53,720 --> 00:04:54,640
I can't say.

141
00:04:54,640 --> 00:04:55,350
You totally did.

142
00:04:55,350 --> 00:04:55,790
Right?

143
00:04:55,790 --> 00:04:56,650
Your face says it all.

144
00:04:59,940 --> 00:05:02,580
(Yang Tinghong is choosing
a dating partner)

145
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:03,200
At first,

146
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:06,190
I actually wanted to date Guan.

147
00:05:06,190 --> 00:05:07,710
(Yang Tinghong, Wu Guanjie)
He...

148
00:05:07,710 --> 00:05:09,510
He's really the type I like.

149
00:05:09,510 --> 00:05:10,390
I'm interested in him.

150
00:05:10,760 --> 00:05:12,950
He's actually a bit like Enda,

151
00:05:13,230 --> 00:05:15,440
quiet, not much of a talker,

152
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:17,550
and kind of passive too.

153
00:05:17,550 --> 00:05:19,670
(Wu Guanjie)
I just get drawn to guys like that.

154
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:22,720
But then I thought it over,

155
00:05:23,440 --> 00:05:25,600
I can't let a fleeting impulse

156
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:27,720
blindly

157
00:05:27,720 --> 00:05:28,830
push me into a decision.

158
00:05:32,380 --> 00:05:36,620
(Yang Tinghong, Zhao Enda)

159
00:05:36,640 --> 00:05:38,440
If I let my impulse
take over for a moment

160
00:05:38,440 --> 00:05:41,230
and miss the chance
to truly get to know Enda,

161
00:05:41,230 --> 00:05:42,320
I'd really regret it.

162
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:45,480
So I need to calm down

163
00:05:45,480 --> 00:05:46,920
and think about my true feeling.

164
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:55,800
Honestly, I'm curious about

165
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:57,480
who you set up for the others.

166
00:05:57,950 --> 00:05:58,500
You.

167
00:05:58,500 --> 00:05:59,550
You set someone up for me?

168
00:05:59,550 --> 00:05:59,880
Yeah.

169
00:06:00,440 --> 00:06:01,510
I want to know whom

170
00:06:01,510 --> 00:06:02,440
you set up for me.

171
00:06:02,440 --> 00:06:03,200
I want you to win.

172
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:04,540
I don't care about winning myself.

173
00:06:04,540 --> 00:06:05,270
I want you to win.

174
00:06:05,270 --> 00:06:06,000
Why?

175
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:08,040
I like the person you matched me with.

176
00:06:08,350 --> 00:06:09,540
You like taking the back seat.

177
00:06:09,760 --> 00:06:11,510
And I trust your taste.

178
00:06:11,580 --> 00:06:15,540
(Lu Yanting's Room)

179
00:06:17,230 --> 00:06:19,880
The Balance Arena is about to open.

180
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:22,830
Everyone,
head to the lawn and form your teams.

181
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:26,920
What?

182
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:28,040
I'm not into the game.

183
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:29,110
We're doing this again?

184
00:06:29,110 --> 00:06:31,000
I don't want to pick anything.

185
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:32,200
Are we picking male partners?

186
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:33,230
Seems like it.

187
00:06:36,880 --> 00:06:38,350
It's actually random?

188
00:06:38,350 --> 00:06:39,640
Like a mystery box.

189
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:49,550
Let these strings decide our fate.

190
00:06:49,830 --> 00:06:51,040
Totally random.

191
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:51,390
No.

192
00:06:51,440 --> 00:06:52,040
Not random.

193
00:06:52,040 --> 00:06:53,950
Call it fate's arrangement.

194
00:06:55,760 --> 00:06:57,160
You pick first.

195
00:06:57,160 --> 00:06:57,570
I'll wait.

196
00:06:57,570 --> 00:06:58,510
Too nervous to choose.

197
00:06:58,510 --> 00:06:59,000
Come on.

198
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:00,160
Or you'll lose your chance.

199
00:07:00,160 --> 00:07:00,640
Hurry up.

200
00:07:00,690 --> 00:07:01,710
Which one are you picking?

201
00:07:01,720 --> 00:07:02,720
I'll go with this one.

202
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:03,510
Okay.

203
00:07:03,510 --> 00:07:04,270
I'll take this one.

204
00:07:04,270 --> 00:07:04,720
Pointless.

205
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:06,200
It's all mixed up inside.

206
00:07:06,320 --> 00:07:08,040
Yeah, it's jumbled.

207
00:07:08,920 --> 00:07:10,390
So it's totally random?

208
00:07:13,440 --> 00:07:14,880
What is this?

209
00:07:16,920 --> 00:07:17,550
This one.

210
00:07:23,390 --> 00:07:24,110
This piece.

211
00:07:24,350 --> 00:07:25,330
I'm sticking with this.

212
00:07:29,440 --> 00:07:31,000
I'll switch to another.

213
00:07:31,230 --> 00:07:32,000
Xuan Cheng.

214
00:07:32,540 --> 00:07:33,550
I want to be next to her.

215
00:07:33,550 --> 00:07:34,550
Let me pick another one.

216
00:07:34,550 --> 00:07:36,640
You guys should match randomly again.

217
00:07:38,950 --> 00:07:39,760
That's impossible.

218
00:07:39,760 --> 00:07:41,230
It's definitely a long detour.

219
00:07:41,230 --> 00:07:42,350
Pick one for me.

220
00:07:42,640 --> 00:07:43,760
I have no idea.

221
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:52,060
I can't feel the difference.

222
00:07:52,060 --> 00:07:53,240
I can't tell just by looking.

223
00:07:57,440 --> 00:07:58,600
Maybe this is the key moment.

224
00:07:59,390 --> 00:07:59,880
You done?

225
00:07:59,880 --> 00:08:01,040
Maybe this is the key moment.

226
00:08:01,390 --> 00:08:02,510
It could change everything.

227
00:08:02,640 --> 00:08:03,600
Yeah, it's all random.

228
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:04,390
That's kind of nice.

229
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:06,100
Let's leave it to fate.

230
00:08:06,600 --> 00:08:08,440
What on earth is this?

231
00:08:10,720 --> 00:08:11,780
Look at this young man,

232
00:08:11,780 --> 00:08:13,440
coming with these two beauties.

233
00:08:15,110 --> 00:08:16,110
It's a blind selection.

234
00:08:16,270 --> 00:08:17,920
Like drawing the red string of destiny.

235
00:08:18,550 --> 00:08:19,350
Two strings left.

236
00:08:19,510 --> 00:08:20,480
This is getting exciting.

237
00:08:28,200 --> 00:08:29,200
I'm going with this one.

238
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:29,440
Okay.

239
00:08:29,440 --> 00:08:30,230
Then this it mine.

240
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:35,280
And Yanting's not here yet.

241
00:08:35,280 --> 00:08:36,230
He's here now.

242
00:08:37,590 --> 00:08:39,030
We kept one spot for Yanting.

243
00:08:39,030 --> 00:08:40,400
So he doesn't really have a choice.

244
00:08:40,840 --> 00:08:41,910
That string is yours.

245
00:08:49,350 --> 00:08:49,910
It hit me

246
00:08:49,910 --> 00:08:50,760
we have seven strings

247
00:08:50,760 --> 00:08:51,640
and they have six.

248
00:08:51,880 --> 00:08:53,320
That means one string has no match.

249
00:08:53,640 --> 00:08:55,150
That would feel pretty awful.

250
00:08:55,710 --> 00:08:56,790
I'm getting a bit nervous.

251
00:08:56,790 --> 00:08:57,550
Me too.

252
00:08:57,550 --> 00:08:58,550
I'm worried I'll draw...

253
00:08:58,550 --> 00:09:01,520
Now, let's announce the pairing rules.

254
00:09:01,520 --> 00:09:03,910
Islanders, line up on opposite sides.

255
00:09:03,910 --> 00:09:05,760
Each of you will pick one red string.

256
00:09:05,760 --> 00:09:08,000
Once everyone pulls their strings straight,

257
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:10,840
the man and woman
holding the same string

258
00:09:10,840 --> 00:09:13,440
will become today's destined partners.

259
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:14,590
The guy who's on his own

260
00:09:14,590 --> 00:09:17,790
is not joining today's challenge.

261
00:09:19,640 --> 00:09:20,080
It's over.

262
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:20,910
Oh my god.

263
00:09:21,030 --> 00:09:22,150
If he's not joining,

264
00:09:22,150 --> 00:09:23,200
he gets nothing.

265
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:24,090
There's still a chance

266
00:09:24,090 --> 00:09:25,320
if a girl picks him.

267
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:27,960
During the red rope pairing,

268
00:09:27,960 --> 00:09:29,760
I wanted to follow my heart

269
00:09:29,760 --> 00:09:30,840
to team up with Yijia.

270
00:09:32,230 --> 00:09:33,400
I didn't have other plans.

271
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:35,640
I'm probably not that good
at these games.

272
00:09:35,640 --> 00:09:37,440
If I ended up drawing Yang,

273
00:09:37,440 --> 00:09:38,880
I was afraid I might slow her down.

274
00:09:39,230 --> 00:09:40,640
I trust fate's way of working.

275
00:09:41,030 --> 00:09:42,350
I was praying

276
00:09:42,350 --> 00:09:44,840
that rope led to Jiayi.

277
00:09:45,350 --> 00:09:47,200
I actually think that's pretty exciting.

278
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:49,350
It's like letting fate take the lead.

279
00:09:49,350 --> 00:09:50,280
Let's leave it to fate.

280
00:09:51,110 --> 00:09:52,200
Can we pull it out now?

281
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:52,840
Okay.

282
00:09:52,840 --> 00:09:53,590
Come on.

283
00:09:53,590 --> 00:09:54,590
Three.

284
00:09:55,520 --> 00:09:56,110
Two.

285
00:09:56,760 --> 00:09:57,520
One.

286
00:10:06,400 --> 00:10:08,150
What on earth is this?

287
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:09,520
Who's my teammate?

288
00:10:13,640 --> 00:10:15,150
This knot's a total mess.

289
00:10:15,250 --> 00:10:16,000
What is this thing?

290
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:17,150
Who's tangled up with who?

291
00:10:17,150 --> 00:10:18,960
He yanked it right out of my hands.

292
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:19,400
Alright.

293
00:10:19,790 --> 00:10:21,350
We'll have to untangle it.

294
00:10:22,640 --> 00:10:23,200
You and me.

295
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:23,590
Really?

296
00:10:23,590 --> 00:10:23,960
Is it?

297
00:10:23,960 --> 00:10:24,400
No idea.

298
00:10:25,710 --> 00:10:27,000
I just feel...

299
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:28,080
it's...

300
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:29,670
(Huang Jiawei & Liu Jiayi)

301
00:10:29,670 --> 00:10:31,000
You're pretty good at this,

302
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,080
sir.

303
00:10:33,400 --> 00:10:34,760
It's kind of surprising, right?

304
00:10:34,760 --> 00:10:36,230
I didn't expect to be his teammate.

305
00:10:36,230 --> 00:10:36,590
But then,

306
00:10:36,590 --> 00:10:38,030
I actually think it's pretty nice.

307
00:10:38,030 --> 00:10:39,320
With him, I'm quite at ease.

308
00:10:39,320 --> 00:10:40,500
Well, he is the village chief.

309
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:41,280
Why us?

310
00:10:41,280 --> 00:10:42,230
You sound reluctant.

311
00:10:42,230 --> 00:10:43,640
I'm not reluctant.

312
00:10:43,640 --> 00:10:45,030
I'm actually really happy about it.

313
00:10:45,910 --> 00:10:46,470
Why?

314
00:10:46,470 --> 00:10:46,780
Anyway,

315
00:10:46,780 --> 00:10:47,790
I'll try my best to win.

316
00:10:48,760 --> 00:10:50,520
I ended up in the same team as Jiayi.

317
00:10:50,840 --> 00:10:52,640
Let's see if I can help her score a win.

318
00:10:52,640 --> 00:10:54,150
And match-make my bro and her.

319
00:10:54,150 --> 00:10:55,000
It's on you now, bro.

320
00:10:56,960 --> 00:10:57,760
I'm with you.

321
00:10:58,030 --> 00:10:59,440
Yes.

322
00:10:59,440 --> 00:11:00,840
(Xuan Cheng & Zhu Huiyan)

323
00:11:00,840 --> 00:11:01,110
Oh no,

324
00:11:01,110 --> 00:11:01,960
my hand's hurt.

325
00:11:02,880 --> 00:11:03,590
What should we do?

326
00:11:03,760 --> 00:11:04,230
It's fine.

327
00:11:04,230 --> 00:11:05,000
I can push through.

328
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:05,760
Okay.

329
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:09,200
Come on.

330
00:11:09,640 --> 00:11:10,320
Get over here.

331
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:12,910
See you.

332
00:11:13,320 --> 00:11:15,400
Let's try to win this together.

333
00:11:15,790 --> 00:11:17,280
(Zhang Zizheng & Yang Tinghong)
Sure.

334
00:11:17,280 --> 00:11:17,840
Try our best.

335
00:11:20,440 --> 00:11:21,350
Seriously,

336
00:11:21,350 --> 00:11:22,520
it's getting chaotic.

337
00:11:22,520 --> 00:11:24,200
What a good match.

338
00:11:25,470 --> 00:11:27,440
(Zhao Enda & Wu Yihan)
Back then, I was hoping to

339
00:11:27,440 --> 00:11:29,640
be teamed up with Zhang Zizheng.

340
00:11:30,150 --> 00:11:31,840
I did feel a little regret about it.

341
00:11:31,840 --> 00:11:33,000
Because at that moment,

342
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:35,230
I saw him standing all the way
at the end.

343
00:11:35,230 --> 00:11:36,520
And I chose to be in the middle.

344
00:11:36,520 --> 00:11:37,330
I remember thinking,

345
00:11:37,330 --> 00:11:38,570
the middle rope might not quite

346
00:11:38,570 --> 00:11:40,230
match the side ones perfectly.

347
00:11:40,230 --> 00:11:41,470
I was actually going to suggest

348
00:11:41,470 --> 00:11:43,030
he switch places with Enda.

349
00:11:43,030 --> 00:11:43,960
But then I thought, nah,

350
00:11:43,960 --> 00:11:45,150
not necessary.

351
00:11:45,150 --> 00:11:47,280
It turned out we just missed it by a bit.

352
00:11:49,110 --> 00:11:50,080
Chen Yijia and I.

353
00:11:51,280 --> 00:11:52,030
We're teammates.

354
00:11:52,030 --> 00:11:53,940
(Yang Tianyu & Chen Yijia)

355
00:11:54,230 --> 00:11:55,640
This kind of grouping...

356
00:11:58,500 --> 00:11:59,590
Those two are seriously...

357
00:11:59,590 --> 00:12:00,520
A true power duo.

358
00:12:01,380 --> 00:12:04,580
(Wu Guanjie & Ding Wanning)

359
00:12:05,960 --> 00:12:07,230
How do we even play this?

360
00:12:08,280 --> 00:12:09,470
This team is seriously wild.

361
00:12:09,910 --> 00:12:10,920
There's no way we can win.

362
00:12:10,920 --> 00:12:11,760
Not a single chance.

363
00:12:11,960 --> 00:12:13,080
So, what's the plan here?

364
00:12:13,470 --> 00:12:14,910
No tug-of-war today.

365
00:12:15,150 --> 00:12:17,080
Feels like we've got no edge
in anything.

366
00:12:17,520 --> 00:12:18,590
They're insanely good.

367
00:12:18,960 --> 00:12:21,230
That duo is pure athletic power.

368
00:12:21,230 --> 00:12:23,030
The pressure just shot way up.

369
00:12:23,030 --> 00:12:23,840
Uh…

370
00:12:24,520 --> 00:12:25,910
He looks seriously strong to me.

371
00:12:25,910 --> 00:12:26,470
I think…

372
00:12:26,910 --> 00:12:27,960
We might win the game.

373
00:12:28,350 --> 00:12:29,960
With the two of us together...

374
00:12:29,960 --> 00:12:31,640
They're probably feeling the heat.

375
00:12:32,910 --> 00:12:33,640
Yanting.

376
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:34,880
I'm alone.

377
00:12:35,610 --> 00:12:36,280
Watch the game.

378
00:12:36,280 --> 00:12:37,130
(Lu Yanting is alone)

379
00:12:37,130 --> 00:12:37,890
The stage is yours.

380
00:12:40,320 --> 00:12:42,200
Why are you by yourself?

381
00:12:45,280 --> 00:12:47,150
I can finally get some sleep.

382
00:12:47,150 --> 00:12:48,440
You came late.

383
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:49,400
Yeah.

384
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:50,760
He's on his own.

385
00:12:52,350 --> 00:12:54,080
It's a bit of a shame for me.

386
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:56,150
I didn't get the chance
to show what I can do.

387
00:12:56,150 --> 00:12:57,910
And I missed a chance

388
00:12:57,910 --> 00:12:59,670
to team up with Jiayi again.

389
00:13:03,470 --> 00:13:06,440
Congrats on
becoming the Destined Partner.

390
00:13:06,440 --> 00:13:10,150
Please get changed
and head to the arena.

391
00:13:10,350 --> 00:13:10,980
Let's do this!

392
00:13:11,110 --> 00:13:12,440
Go, go, go!

393
00:13:12,440 --> 00:13:13,280
Let's go!

394
00:13:13,280 --> 00:13:14,350
Give it your all!

395
00:13:17,320 --> 00:13:18,080
Ready?

396
00:13:18,080 --> 00:13:18,760
Ready!

397
00:13:18,760 --> 00:13:19,440
Let's go.

398
00:13:23,760 --> 00:13:24,710
Hat snatching game?

399
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:26,670
Jiawei.

400
00:13:27,550 --> 00:13:28,320
You lost.

401
00:13:29,030 --> 00:13:29,550
Really?

402
00:13:31,640 --> 00:13:33,030
As long as we don't use our hands.

403
00:13:33,030 --> 00:13:35,880
I think I can still hold my own
against them.

404
00:13:36,470 --> 00:13:37,670
Go for it.

405
00:13:37,910 --> 00:13:38,710
Come on.

406
00:13:38,710 --> 00:13:39,910
High five.

407
00:13:39,910 --> 00:13:40,150
Go.

408
00:13:40,150 --> 00:13:40,710
Come on.

409
00:13:40,960 --> 00:13:41,860
I'm feeling so pumped.

410
00:13:41,860 --> 00:13:42,550
Gotta be.

411
00:13:43,110 --> 00:13:44,280
Are you ready?

412
00:13:47,110 --> 00:13:48,150
Why didn't you ask me?

413
00:13:48,150 --> 00:13:48,550
Right.

414
00:13:48,550 --> 00:13:49,790
I thought you were asking me.

415
00:13:50,710 --> 00:13:51,520
Are you ready?

416
00:13:52,470 --> 00:13:53,280
Nope?

417
00:13:55,840 --> 00:13:56,470
Are you ready?

418
00:14:01,910 --> 00:14:02,710
Let's do this.

419
00:14:07,960 --> 00:14:08,960
Are we running too fast?

420
00:14:08,960 --> 00:14:09,550
We have to

421
00:14:09,550 --> 00:14:10,320
pick up the pace.

422
00:14:10,320 --> 00:14:11,400
Leave the island ASAP.

423
00:14:13,880 --> 00:14:14,670
What?

424
00:14:15,550 --> 00:14:16,350
Hats?

425
00:14:21,350 --> 00:14:23,590
They look amazing running like that.

426
00:14:31,030 --> 00:14:31,910
So beautiful.

427
00:14:31,910 --> 00:14:33,080
That's incredible.

428
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:33,960
Wow.

429
00:14:34,110 --> 00:14:35,960
Is this an advert for a sports brand?

430
00:14:39,960 --> 00:14:42,000
She looks perfect in sportswear.

431
00:14:47,350 --> 00:14:49,910
I couldn't join the action.

432
00:14:49,910 --> 00:14:51,880
Figured I could be the assistant,

433
00:14:51,880 --> 00:14:53,670
like a cheer squad support role,

434
00:14:53,670 --> 00:14:55,320
handing out umbrellas

435
00:14:55,320 --> 00:14:56,440
and water.

436
00:14:57,350 --> 00:14:58,230
Most importantly...

437
00:14:58,230 --> 00:15:00,110
Of course, I can look after Jiayi.

438
00:15:01,840 --> 00:15:03,180
Logistics team, let's welcome him.

439
00:15:03,320 --> 00:15:03,960
Here they come.

440
00:15:03,960 --> 00:15:04,840
Welcome.

441
00:15:05,230 --> 00:15:06,150
Thank you.

442
00:15:06,150 --> 00:15:07,470
I'm at your call.

443
00:15:07,470 --> 00:15:08,280
Alright.

444
00:15:08,280 --> 00:15:08,880
That's great.

445
00:15:09,080 --> 00:15:12,550
We're starting the Hat Guard Battle.

446
00:15:12,550 --> 00:15:13,640
Each team will

447
00:15:13,640 --> 00:15:16,280
tie their wrists together with the rope.

448
00:15:16,280 --> 00:15:17,760
The girl wears the hat

449
00:15:17,760 --> 00:15:19,470
and tries to snatch hats

450
00:15:19,470 --> 00:15:21,280
from other girls during the game.

451
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:23,760
The guy's job is to protect her.

452
00:15:23,760 --> 00:15:25,710
But he can't grab hats himself.

453
00:15:25,710 --> 00:15:29,350
If her hat falls,
that team is out immediately.

454
00:15:29,350 --> 00:15:30,350
The last team

455
00:15:30,350 --> 00:15:33,670
with their hat still on wins.

456
00:15:35,350 --> 00:15:36,000
Got it.

457
00:15:36,880 --> 00:15:38,200
When I learned about the rules,

458
00:15:38,200 --> 00:15:39,840
I really wanted to win.

459
00:15:40,320 --> 00:15:41,760
I felt like I had a strong edge.

460
00:15:42,280 --> 00:15:42,710
Because

461
00:15:42,710 --> 00:15:46,230
hat snatching is actually
tied to height.

462
00:15:46,230 --> 00:15:48,440
How about we let them "battle"
for a bit first,

463
00:15:48,440 --> 00:15:48,960
and then...?

464
00:15:48,960 --> 00:15:49,400
Let's hide.

465
00:15:49,400 --> 00:15:49,960
Yeah.

466
00:15:50,520 --> 00:15:53,550
Ladies, please put on your hats now.

467
00:15:55,230 --> 00:15:56,320
Let me help you with that.

468
00:15:59,520 --> 00:16:01,320
Do you want to tuck your ponytail in?

469
00:16:01,320 --> 00:16:02,550
Sure.

470
00:16:02,550 --> 00:16:02,960
Like this.

471
00:16:02,960 --> 00:16:03,960
But it might pull on you.

472
00:16:03,960 --> 00:16:04,440
It's fine.

473
00:16:04,440 --> 00:16:06,280
I'm okay with it.

474
00:16:06,280 --> 00:16:08,080
Even if it all falls out,
that's okay.

475
00:16:24,320 --> 00:16:25,640
All set.

476
00:16:26,320 --> 00:16:27,150
Alright, first off.

477
00:16:27,150 --> 00:16:27,640
Come on.

478
00:16:30,710 --> 00:16:31,910
Tighten it as much as you can.

479
00:16:32,910 --> 00:16:33,520
Is this enough?

480
00:16:33,520 --> 00:16:34,280
Yeah, that's good.

481
00:16:37,150 --> 00:16:38,550
We could go ask them ourselves.

482
00:16:39,350 --> 00:16:40,350
We can just ask them

483
00:16:40,350 --> 00:16:41,150
to form an alliance.

484
00:16:44,150 --> 00:16:45,110
Wanna team up?

485
00:16:45,400 --> 00:16:46,230
Let's deal with them.

486
00:16:48,110 --> 00:16:49,110
So it'll be three teams?

487
00:16:49,110 --> 00:16:50,000
Is that okay?

488
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:50,470
Sure.

489
00:16:50,960 --> 00:16:52,590
They're kind of strong over there.

490
00:16:53,590 --> 00:16:55,520
Wan kinda intimidates me.

491
00:17:00,440 --> 00:17:01,520
Let's join forces.

492
00:17:01,520 --> 00:17:02,110
Join forces?

493
00:17:03,110 --> 00:17:03,710
Han.

494
00:17:06,040 --> 00:17:06,800
Teaming up, right?

495
00:17:07,110 --> 00:17:07,590
Sounds good.

496
00:17:08,160 --> 00:17:09,710
But we should bring him into the team.

497
00:17:09,710 --> 00:17:10,070
Who?

498
00:17:10,640 --> 00:17:11,280
Them.

499
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:13,760
Come on.

500
00:17:14,190 --> 00:17:15,190
Let's team up.

501
00:17:15,190 --> 00:17:15,920
What do you mean?

502
00:17:15,920 --> 00:17:16,760
Let's just

503
00:17:16,760 --> 00:17:18,280
take them out first.

504
00:17:18,470 --> 00:17:19,430
Sounds good.

505
00:17:19,430 --> 00:17:19,830
Sure.

506
00:17:20,560 --> 00:17:22,010
You've got plenty of advantages.

507
00:17:22,010 --> 00:17:22,820
You're really tall.

508
00:17:22,820 --> 00:17:23,990
Your reach gives you an edge.

509
00:17:23,990 --> 00:17:25,520
Let's not mess with them yet.

510
00:17:25,520 --> 00:17:26,760
That group of...

511
00:17:26,760 --> 00:17:27,640
The strongest one.

512
00:17:27,640 --> 00:17:28,110
Black hat?

513
00:17:28,110 --> 00:17:28,810
Don't go after it.

514
00:17:29,400 --> 00:17:31,400
The one in black
will guard red and orange.

515
00:17:31,400 --> 00:17:32,520
They've formed an alliance.

516
00:17:32,760 --> 00:17:34,160
But the red one's easier to grab

517
00:17:34,160 --> 00:17:35,590
since she's not that tall.

518
00:17:35,590 --> 00:17:36,160
The red one?

519
00:17:36,160 --> 00:17:37,560
Yeah,it's slightly easier to take.

520
00:17:40,560 --> 00:17:41,880
I feel like they're watching me.

521
00:17:41,880 --> 00:17:42,520
What's the plan?

522
00:17:43,520 --> 00:17:44,410
You're the smallest.

523
00:17:44,640 --> 00:17:46,040
You're the easiest to pick off.

524
00:17:46,520 --> 00:17:47,350
Then we should

525
00:17:47,350 --> 00:17:48,070
target one first.

526
00:17:48,520 --> 00:17:50,430
I think their plan is
to grab my hat first.

527
00:17:50,640 --> 00:17:51,820
So if they come for me,

528
00:17:51,820 --> 00:17:52,520
you guys can wait.

529
00:17:52,520 --> 00:17:53,360
If there's a chance

530
00:17:53,360 --> 00:17:54,980
and someone's alone,
just take them out.

531
00:17:55,230 --> 00:17:56,880
Let's deal with that white hat first.

532
00:17:58,830 --> 00:17:59,560
Here is the plan.

533
00:18:00,430 --> 00:18:02,110
Because we two are both relatively

534
00:18:02,110 --> 00:18:03,160
a bit bigger in size,

535
00:18:03,160 --> 00:18:04,040
we can hold them off.

536
00:18:04,040 --> 00:18:05,560
Then you had the village chef

537
00:18:05,560 --> 00:18:07,760
take you around the back.

538
00:18:07,760 --> 00:18:08,430
And me.

539
00:18:08,430 --> 00:18:09,190
What about me?

540
00:18:09,190 --> 00:18:10,310
You two just hid.

541
00:18:10,310 --> 00:18:12,070
We were ready to face them head-on.

542
00:18:12,710 --> 00:18:14,710
It's easy to say that now.

543
00:18:14,710 --> 00:18:15,800
But when the game starts,

544
00:18:15,800 --> 00:18:16,560
things get messy.

545
00:18:16,560 --> 00:18:18,110
That's why we need to stick to the plan.

546
00:18:21,110 --> 00:18:22,400
We team up with them for this.

547
00:18:23,110 --> 00:18:24,110
But I think

548
00:18:24,470 --> 00:18:26,520
we shouldn't push too far ahead.

549
00:18:26,710 --> 00:18:28,880
If we're too far forward,
the back opens up.

550
00:18:28,880 --> 00:18:29,430
Alright.

551
00:18:29,760 --> 00:18:30,800
Yeah, so at the start...

552
00:18:30,800 --> 00:18:32,640
He said we'd attack with the white hat.

553
00:18:32,640 --> 00:18:33,880
We should stay back a little.

554
00:18:34,640 --> 00:18:35,470
Yeah, you're right.

555
00:18:35,470 --> 00:18:35,880
Sure.

556
00:18:36,400 --> 00:18:36,760
Then I...

557
00:18:36,760 --> 00:18:38,760
Should we hold our hands
or leave it like this?

558
00:18:38,760 --> 00:18:39,390
Both are fine.

559
00:18:39,670 --> 00:18:40,110
Okay.

560
00:18:54,070 --> 00:18:56,000
Maybe if I keep my hand here,

561
00:18:56,000 --> 00:18:57,830
will it block your move?

562
00:18:57,830 --> 00:18:58,400
No, it won't.

563
00:18:58,400 --> 00:19:00,110
I think we have that unspoken sync.

564
00:19:06,640 --> 00:19:08,640
Village chief, what's your strategy?

565
00:19:08,640 --> 00:19:09,780
No clue, they're discussing.

566
00:19:10,430 --> 00:19:11,230
So what's your plan?

567
00:19:11,830 --> 00:19:13,400
I think you should make the first move.

568
00:19:14,430 --> 00:19:15,230
I'll go first?

569
00:19:16,310 --> 00:19:16,680
Who?

570
00:19:16,680 --> 00:19:17,520
Get him eliminated.

571
00:19:17,520 --> 00:19:18,160
Angus?

572
00:19:18,590 --> 00:19:20,230
Honestly, I kinda want him to win.

573
00:19:20,230 --> 00:19:21,070
Why?

574
00:19:21,070 --> 00:19:22,520
Because if he...

575
00:19:22,520 --> 00:19:24,880
and she goes out on a date…

576
00:19:24,880 --> 00:19:26,160
I had the chance to reach out

577
00:19:27,470 --> 00:19:28,850
to others...

578
00:19:28,850 --> 00:19:29,680
I'll have a chance.

579
00:19:29,680 --> 00:19:30,190
You sure?

580
00:19:30,520 --> 00:19:31,430
Yeah.

581
00:19:31,430 --> 00:19:32,310
I wanted him to win.

582
00:19:32,310 --> 00:19:32,950
Okay.

583
00:19:36,920 --> 00:19:38,110
During the match today,

584
00:19:38,110 --> 00:19:39,470
I already had a hunch

585
00:19:39,470 --> 00:19:41,640
about the result of their date list.

586
00:19:41,640 --> 00:19:43,430
I thought either let Yijia win,

587
00:19:43,430 --> 00:19:45,230
so I could see who she picked,

588
00:19:45,430 --> 00:19:47,280
or let Enda win.

589
00:19:50,560 --> 00:19:51,560
I was rooting for Han.

590
00:19:51,560 --> 00:19:53,470
It was actually a bit of a gamble.

591
00:19:54,110 --> 00:19:54,830
I wanted to see

592
00:19:54,830 --> 00:19:56,160
if she really was

593
00:19:56,160 --> 00:19:57,430
genuinely interested in me.

594
00:19:57,640 --> 00:19:59,470
If she really chose me,

595
00:19:59,470 --> 00:19:59,920
then okay.

596
00:19:59,920 --> 00:20:00,350
Then...

597
00:20:01,280 --> 00:20:01,560
Right?

598
00:20:01,560 --> 00:20:02,230
Everyone's happy.

599
00:20:02,230 --> 00:20:03,680
I'll know exactly how she feels.

600
00:20:03,680 --> 00:20:06,310
I might gain a clearer understanding

601
00:20:06,310 --> 00:20:07,830
of who on the island I should

602
00:20:08,300 --> 00:20:08,950
fully commit to.

603
00:20:13,040 --> 00:20:15,160
This date really matters to me.

604
00:20:18,100 --> 00:20:24,260
(Wu Yihan, Zhang Zizheng)

605
00:20:25,160 --> 00:20:26,800
I want to go on a date.

606
00:20:30,800 --> 00:20:31,760
Okay.

607
00:20:31,760 --> 00:20:33,110
I can feel it.

608
00:20:36,710 --> 00:20:37,710
I want to win.

609
00:20:38,830 --> 00:20:39,590
I'll let you win.

610
00:20:40,310 --> 00:20:41,110
Counting on you.

611
00:20:42,680 --> 00:20:44,560
We all want you to go on that date.

612
00:20:45,560 --> 00:20:47,190
Should it be tied tighter or looser?

613
00:20:47,520 --> 00:20:48,110
Looser.

614
00:20:48,640 --> 00:20:49,350
There we go.

615
00:20:49,500 --> 00:20:50,280
We just need to...

616
00:20:50,280 --> 00:20:51,160
Don't let it slip off.

617
00:20:51,160 --> 00:20:51,710
Yeah.

618
00:20:55,470 --> 00:20:55,950
Like this?

619
00:21:00,950 --> 00:21:02,200
Should it be looser or tighter?

620
00:21:02,470 --> 00:21:03,040
Tighter.

621
00:21:03,710 --> 00:21:04,640
Why?

622
00:21:04,640 --> 00:21:05,040
We can

623
00:21:05,040 --> 00:21:06,430
keep more distance if it's loose.

624
00:21:06,430 --> 00:21:07,800
But if it slips out, you lose.

625
00:21:08,430 --> 00:21:10,040
If you hold hands, it won't slip out.

626
00:21:10,230 --> 00:21:11,350
The chance is small.

627
00:21:11,350 --> 00:21:13,160
Though there's still a chance...

628
00:21:13,160 --> 00:21:15,160
The rule says you have to hold hands.

629
00:21:23,430 --> 00:21:24,830
At first, I didn't...

630
00:21:24,830 --> 00:21:26,760
I didn't think we had to
hold that tightly.

631
00:21:26,760 --> 00:21:28,710
I thought just a light grip was fine.

632
00:21:29,070 --> 00:21:30,040
But when I turned around,

633
00:21:30,040 --> 00:21:32,520
I saw Enda and Han locking fingers.

634
00:21:32,520 --> 00:21:33,760
It kinda startled me.

635
00:21:34,280 --> 00:21:36,070
I can ask him about it after the game.

636
00:21:36,070 --> 00:21:37,830
What are his own feelings?

637
00:21:38,230 --> 00:21:39,640
Was there a moment when he felt...

638
00:21:39,640 --> 00:21:41,310
that heart-racing flutter?

639
00:21:44,680 --> 00:21:44,940
Okay.

640
00:21:44,940 --> 00:21:45,690
I'll hold her hand.

641
00:21:45,690 --> 00:21:46,880
Sure, that's fine.

642
00:21:47,070 --> 00:21:47,470
Okay.

643
00:21:47,920 --> 00:21:48,800
Because this way,

644
00:21:49,190 --> 00:21:51,400
it's easier to keep her safe.

645
00:21:51,680 --> 00:21:51,950
Got it.

646
00:22:10,640 --> 00:22:11,680
Wan.

647
00:22:13,540 --> 00:22:14,190
You've got this.

648
00:22:14,190 --> 00:22:14,760
Come on.

649
00:22:30,640 --> 00:22:32,040
Hat Guard Battle

650
00:22:32,040 --> 00:22:33,560
starts now.

651
00:22:39,520 --> 00:22:40,310
Don't stay too close

652
00:22:40,590 --> 00:22:42,160
to the corner, it's hard to escape.

653
00:22:46,560 --> 00:22:47,230
Keep it up.

654
00:22:47,560 --> 00:22:48,430
Go for red first?

655
00:22:48,430 --> 00:22:49,230
Sure.

656
00:22:49,230 --> 00:22:50,000
Head straight.

657
00:22:57,920 --> 00:22:58,520
Here they come.

658
00:22:58,520 --> 00:22:59,280
All are after me.

659
00:22:59,920 --> 00:23:00,640
Fine.

660
00:23:01,520 --> 00:23:02,400
They're coming for me.

661
00:23:03,520 --> 00:23:04,190
Move ahead.

662
00:23:08,560 --> 00:23:09,830
They're in perfect formation.

663
00:23:09,830 --> 00:23:11,040
Why is that?

664
00:23:16,110 --> 00:23:17,450
They're starting to circle around.

665
00:23:18,560 --> 00:23:19,520
Let's hit the red first.

666
00:23:19,520 --> 00:23:20,350
Go.

667
00:23:20,350 --> 00:23:21,110
Move.

668
00:23:22,160 --> 00:23:22,950
Here they come.

669
00:23:24,210 --> 00:23:25,190
She's a bit on its own.

670
00:23:25,190 --> 00:23:25,560
No good.

671
00:23:25,560 --> 00:23:26,880
You need to cover her.

672
00:23:29,760 --> 00:23:30,520
Over there.

673
00:23:31,280 --> 00:23:31,710
That way.

674
00:23:35,710 --> 00:23:36,430
Who's your target?

675
00:23:36,430 --> 00:23:37,430
The white hat.

676
00:23:38,950 --> 00:23:40,040
Alright, they're coming.

677
00:23:40,040 --> 00:23:40,470
Oh no,

678
00:23:40,470 --> 00:23:40,880
let's go.

679
00:23:42,070 --> 00:23:42,920
Go this way.

680
00:23:50,430 --> 00:23:51,400
Head that direction.

681
00:23:53,800 --> 00:23:54,520
I think

682
00:23:54,520 --> 00:23:55,710
let's grab Yan first.

683
00:24:00,110 --> 00:24:01,040
Keep moving.

684
00:24:03,710 --> 00:24:04,520
Escape from the back.

685
00:24:04,520 --> 00:24:05,280
Loop back in.

686
00:24:05,280 --> 00:24:06,280
Circle to the rear.

687
00:24:07,590 --> 00:24:08,830
Guan, pick up the pace a bit.

688
00:24:11,110 --> 00:24:11,930
I've got him blocked.

689
00:24:13,710 --> 00:24:14,560
Get Yan.

690
00:24:17,230 --> 00:24:18,160
Grab Yan.

691
00:24:40,400 --> 00:24:41,310
Nice one.

692
00:24:46,830 --> 00:24:47,640
Perfect.

693
00:24:48,880 --> 00:24:49,950
Honestly, it's just like…

694
00:24:49,950 --> 00:24:51,710
It's over in a single move.

695
00:24:51,710 --> 00:24:53,640
Whoever knocks the other out wins.

696
00:24:53,640 --> 00:24:55,760
Maybe I was just a bit short on luck.

697
00:24:56,470 --> 00:24:59,070
But either way,
it still feels kinda silly.

698
00:25:00,230 --> 00:25:01,000
Sorry, babe.

699
00:25:03,590 --> 00:25:04,680
It's okay.

700
00:25:04,680 --> 00:25:05,230
Sorry.

701
00:25:05,640 --> 00:25:06,950
Then let's go watch the match.

702
00:25:10,830 --> 00:25:11,830
Let's head over there.

703
00:25:14,830 --> 00:25:15,760
I really didn't expect

704
00:25:15,760 --> 00:25:17,040
to be the first one out.

705
00:25:17,760 --> 00:25:19,560
Guess that means no date for me.

706
00:25:19,560 --> 00:25:21,040
And if Yang wins,

707
00:25:21,040 --> 00:25:22,230
she might end up dating Guan.

708
00:25:23,470 --> 00:25:24,110
Oh, it's...

709
00:25:25,520 --> 00:25:25,950
Hold on.

710
00:25:25,950 --> 00:25:26,470
Don't move.

711
00:25:30,560 --> 00:25:31,280
Wait here.

712
00:25:31,590 --> 00:25:32,280
So we're waiting?

713
00:25:32,280 --> 00:25:33,120
When he rushes over,

714
00:25:33,400 --> 00:25:34,470
we'll slip across.

715
00:25:35,760 --> 00:25:37,680
I just realized
Guan's grou is the smartest.

716
00:25:37,680 --> 00:25:38,550
They've been avoiding

717
00:25:38,550 --> 00:25:38,950
the fight.

718
00:25:38,950 --> 00:25:39,640
Exactly.

719
00:25:39,640 --> 00:25:39,950
Yeah.

720
00:25:39,950 --> 00:25:40,400
Because...

721
00:25:40,590 --> 00:25:41,560
he's saving his energy.

722
00:25:41,560 --> 00:25:42,110
Right.

723
00:25:42,940 --> 00:25:43,810
He's always like that.

724
00:25:46,900 --> 00:25:49,820
(Five teams remain on the field)

725
00:25:49,880 --> 00:25:51,040
They're so strong.

726
00:25:53,280 --> 00:25:54,640
I think Yijia's easy
to take down.

727
00:25:55,310 --> 00:25:56,070
It's not that hard.

728
00:25:56,070 --> 00:25:56,710
She's right.

729
00:25:57,040 --> 00:25:57,950
Let's hit Yijia first.

730
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:11,590
Go, Jiawei!

731
00:26:12,070 --> 00:26:12,560
Go, Jiayi!

732
00:26:12,560 --> 00:26:12,990
Don't run!

733
00:26:12,990 --> 00:26:13,780
That's our strategy.

734
00:26:16,830 --> 00:26:18,680
Red hat.

735
00:26:18,680 --> 00:26:19,710
What red hat?

736
00:26:19,710 --> 00:26:20,640
I heard it.

737
00:26:25,280 --> 00:26:26,040
Don't go up.

738
00:26:26,710 --> 00:26:27,800
They've got backup.

739
00:26:39,800 --> 00:26:40,830
Watch out for those two.

740
00:26:48,470 --> 00:26:49,560
Keep an eye on those two.

741
00:26:51,470 --> 00:26:52,640
Don't be scared.

742
00:26:58,950 --> 00:27:00,070
Watch out.

743
00:27:06,280 --> 00:27:06,880
Right side!

744
00:27:08,070 --> 00:27:08,800
On your right!

745
00:27:18,710 --> 00:27:19,430
Move!

746
00:27:19,430 --> 00:27:20,230
Run!

747
00:27:21,710 --> 00:27:22,430
Move!

748
00:27:22,430 --> 00:27:23,230
Run!

749
00:27:25,520 --> 00:27:26,040
Hold on.

750
00:27:26,040 --> 00:27:27,070
It's fine.

751
00:27:27,640 --> 00:27:28,280
I'm fine.

752
00:27:28,470 --> 00:27:29,430
No injuries.

753
00:27:29,430 --> 00:27:30,040
All good.

754
00:27:32,070 --> 00:27:33,040
No problem.

755
00:27:34,430 --> 00:27:34,880
You okay?

756
00:27:34,880 --> 00:27:35,830
It's fine.

757
00:27:40,520 --> 00:27:41,350
They've split up.

758
00:27:41,350 --> 00:27:42,640
We'll rush in right away.

759
00:27:42,830 --> 00:27:43,640
We move separately.

760
00:27:51,230 --> 00:27:51,830
Let's attack.

761
00:27:51,830 --> 00:27:52,520
No other choice.

762
00:28:09,430 --> 00:28:10,350
Go, go!

763
00:28:12,230 --> 00:28:13,350
You got this, Jiayi.

764
00:28:13,350 --> 00:28:14,310
Come on.

765
00:28:14,310 --> 00:28:14,590
Go!

766
00:28:15,350 --> 00:28:16,280
Go!

767
00:28:43,830 --> 00:28:45,520
It's okay, you did your best.

768
00:28:48,640 --> 00:28:49,590
I've been worried

769
00:28:49,590 --> 00:28:50,760
whether Jiayi got hurt.

770
00:28:51,040 --> 00:28:53,640
It was a bit of a shame
when she got eliminated.

771
00:28:53,640 --> 00:28:56,560
But I still told her it's alright.

772
00:28:56,560 --> 00:28:57,230
Because

773
00:28:57,230 --> 00:29:01,070
she'd be less likely to
get injured on the field.

774
00:29:01,070 --> 00:29:03,470
And if she didn't win,

775
00:29:03,470 --> 00:29:04,860
we might also have some other ways

776
00:29:04,860 --> 00:29:06,830
directions to get close to each other.

777
00:29:07,640 --> 00:29:08,230
Thanks.

778
00:29:08,230 --> 00:29:08,760
You okay?

779
00:29:09,520 --> 00:29:10,190
Sorry about that.

780
00:29:10,190 --> 00:29:11,590
No problem.

781
00:29:12,710 --> 00:29:13,880
It's my bad.

782
00:29:15,230 --> 00:29:16,880
I thought my moves were kinda weird.

783
00:29:25,560 --> 00:29:26,520
Come on, you got this!

784
00:29:32,760 --> 00:29:34,230
Want some water?

785
00:29:44,260 --> 00:29:46,420
(Chen Yijia's hat fell)
We lost.

786
00:29:46,430 --> 00:29:46,900
What?

787
00:29:46,900 --> 00:29:47,880
When did yours fall off?

788
00:29:47,880 --> 00:29:48,760
Who

789
00:29:48,760 --> 00:29:49,230
did that?

790
00:29:49,230 --> 00:29:50,070
Wan.

791
00:29:53,040 --> 00:29:53,560
We're doomed.

792
00:29:53,560 --> 00:29:55,000
We've all been taken out.

793
00:29:55,400 --> 00:29:56,230
(Two minutes earlier)

794
00:29:56,230 --> 00:29:57,040
They've split up.

795
00:29:57,040 --> 00:29:58,430
We'll rush in right away.

796
00:29:58,430 --> 00:29:59,350
We move separately.

797
00:29:59,830 --> 00:30:00,470
The blue one.

798
00:30:00,830 --> 00:30:01,560
Look to the left.

799
00:30:03,040 --> 00:30:03,880
Go.

800
00:30:03,880 --> 00:30:04,760
Block it.

801
00:30:04,760 --> 00:30:05,680
Come on.

802
00:30:05,680 --> 00:30:06,310
This way.

803
00:30:11,160 --> 00:30:11,760
Go.

804
00:30:29,070 --> 00:30:30,060
Sorry.

805
00:30:30,060 --> 00:30:30,520
It's fine.

806
00:30:30,520 --> 00:30:30,950
Sorry.

807
00:30:30,950 --> 00:30:32,190
Well done.

808
00:30:32,190 --> 00:30:32,710
Succeed?

809
00:30:36,760 --> 00:30:38,230
It feels like a shame.

810
00:30:38,230 --> 00:30:39,350
I can't go out on a date

811
00:30:39,760 --> 00:30:41,680
and miss out on
some time alone together.

812
00:30:43,880 --> 00:30:45,190
The date I wrote down was you.

813
00:30:45,900 --> 00:30:47,140
The date I wrote down was you.

814
00:30:47,920 --> 00:30:48,430
Yeah?

815
00:30:49,160 --> 00:30:50,070
There's no chance now.

816
00:30:50,560 --> 00:30:51,710
But it's fine.

817
00:30:53,830 --> 00:30:56,230
I thought I wore it pretty tight.

818
00:31:02,350 --> 00:31:04,070
Alright, they're going after their allies.

819
00:31:05,660 --> 00:31:08,980
(Only three teams left on the field)

820
00:31:09,040 --> 00:31:10,640
It's down to the three of us now.

821
00:31:11,830 --> 00:31:13,040
Might be two-on-one for real.

822
00:31:13,680 --> 00:31:14,470
We only…

823
00:31:14,470 --> 00:31:15,400
We only target the Black.

824
00:31:16,070 --> 00:31:16,520
Alright.

825
00:31:17,080 --> 00:31:18,230
Take Guanjie's team out first.

826
00:31:20,760 --> 00:31:22,280
Those two are ganging up on me.

827
00:31:22,280 --> 00:31:23,230
I'll block the Orange.

828
00:31:23,430 --> 00:31:24,160
Double kill.

829
00:31:24,430 --> 00:31:25,310
You block the Red.

830
00:31:25,830 --> 00:31:27,040
I bet Guanjie wins again.

831
00:31:27,040 --> 00:31:28,230
For the date, guys!

832
00:31:28,230 --> 00:31:29,350
For the date!

833
00:31:39,680 --> 00:31:40,680
Look over there.

834
00:31:48,680 --> 00:31:49,830
They should team up to take

835
00:31:49,830 --> 00:31:50,560
Wan down first.

836
00:31:50,560 --> 00:31:51,110
Yeah.

837
00:31:51,110 --> 00:31:51,760
Target Wan.

838
00:31:51,950 --> 00:31:52,640
What?

839
00:31:53,160 --> 00:31:53,950
Look over there.

840
00:31:57,110 --> 00:31:58,880
Both teams came after me at that point.

841
00:31:59,190 --> 00:32:00,830
It was hard to attack, but

842
00:32:08,560 --> 00:32:09,880
they were the ones under pressure.

843
00:32:11,680 --> 00:32:13,190
Her arms are way too long.

844
00:32:13,190 --> 00:32:14,110
She's got such an edge.

845
00:32:14,110 --> 00:32:14,830
Such an edge.

846
00:32:14,830 --> 00:32:15,920
Yeah, exactly.

847
00:32:16,280 --> 00:32:17,110
Sorry.

848
00:32:17,880 --> 00:32:18,470
You okay?

849
00:32:18,470 --> 00:32:19,470
The whole time was...

850
00:32:19,470 --> 00:32:20,070
Sorry.

851
00:32:20,070 --> 00:32:21,040
It's fine.

852
00:32:23,830 --> 00:32:25,040
Come on.

853
00:32:25,040 --> 00:32:25,830
Keep going.

854
00:32:26,560 --> 00:32:27,280
Good job.

855
00:32:27,830 --> 00:32:28,520
Yang.

856
00:32:29,640 --> 00:32:30,880
She's so hard to beat.

857
00:32:31,230 --> 00:32:32,000
Sit for a bit.

858
00:32:32,470 --> 00:32:34,000
Well done.

859
00:32:34,880 --> 00:32:35,470
Are you hurt?

860
00:32:35,470 --> 00:32:36,230
No, I'm fine.

861
00:32:36,230 --> 00:32:37,110
Good job.

862
00:32:39,750 --> 00:32:41,190
What's meant to happen will happen.

863
00:32:42,580 --> 00:32:47,100
(2 teams left: Black: Ding Wanning, Wu Guanjie;
Yellow: Wu Yihan, Zhao Enda)

864
00:32:47,110 --> 00:32:48,680
Who are we betting on?

865
00:32:48,680 --> 00:32:49,880
I want to bet on Han.

866
00:32:49,880 --> 00:32:50,470
Really?

867
00:32:55,520 --> 00:32:58,160
I felt the pressure right then.

868
00:32:58,160 --> 00:32:59,070
Because I thought

869
00:32:59,070 --> 00:33:02,950
Han would choose to date
my second brother,

870
00:33:02,950 --> 00:33:04,070
Zizheng.

871
00:33:04,070 --> 00:33:06,280
And I felt she really needed
this chance,

872
00:33:06,280 --> 00:33:08,160
so I wanted Han to win badly.

873
00:33:08,160 --> 00:33:10,880
Besides, Han and Jiayi are roommates.

874
00:33:10,880 --> 00:33:11,350
So

875
00:33:11,350 --> 00:33:12,560
it's very likely to arrange

876
00:33:12,560 --> 00:33:14,190
